cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SD 

This paper discusses the development of an ontology to describe social media users' topics of interest and expertise, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques (cs.CL, cs.IR). The ontology is also designed to be used for interest modeling and text labeling applications, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social informatics (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the ontology's coverage against common social media interest sets, which suggests a focus on data analysis and machine learning (cs.SD).
